subsection.p:
In Practice 1, the rabbit population doubled every 3 months, leading to the growth law
        P(t)=20(2)^{t/3}
Notice how the 3 of "every 3 months" appears in the formula. Now suppose we would like to know the monthly growth factor for the rabbit population, that is, by what factor did the population grow every month?

